      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add context-engine host capability requirements",
        "body": "## What\nThis PR adds a host compatibility contract for context engines, uses it to block unsupported runtime/harness combinations with a descriptive error, and teaches `openclaw doctor` how to repair configs that select an incompatible context engine globally.\n\n## Why\n`lossless-claw` needs OpenClaw to assemble context before the model prompt. Generic CLI-style harnesses do not provide that behavior, so allowing them to boot with `lossless-claw` produces broken runtime behavior instead of a clear configuration failure.\n\n## Changes\n- Add context-engine host requirement metadata\n- Advertise native Codex and Pi capabilities\n- Reject unsupported agent-run hosts early\n- Add doctor preview and repair checks\n- Preserve mixed-runtime configs with warnings\n\n## Testing\n- `pnpm test src/context-engine/host-compat.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/context-engine-host-compat.test.ts src/commands/doctor/repair-sequencing.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/preview-warnings.test.ts` - passed, 4 files / 46 tests across 3 shards.\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` - passed.\n- `pnpm lint:core` - passed.\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check` - passed.\n- `pnpm build` - passed.\n- `launchctl kickstart -k gui/501/ai.openclaw.gateway` - restarted the live gateway from the rebased build.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n### Unsupported Host\n- Scenario: a context engine declares `agent-run.requiredCapabilities = [\"assemble-before-prompt\"]`; a generic CLI host has no pre-prompt assembly capability.\n- Command/path exercised: focused host compatibility tests and the agent-run prepare path.\n- Observed result: OpenClaw raises a descriptive missing-capability error before launch.\n\n### Supported Hosts\n- Scenario: the same host requirement is evaluated for native Codex and Pi embedded host capabilities.\n- Command/path exercised: focused host compatibility tests plus live local gateway startup with `plugins.slots.contextEngine = \"lossless-claw\"`.\n- Observed result: native Codex and Pi satisfy `assemble-before-prompt`; the live gateway starts with `lossless-claw` selected.\n\n```text\n$ node dist/index.js config get plugins.slots.contextEngine\nlossless-claw\n\n$ launchctl print gui/501/ai.openclaw.gateway | rg -n \"state|pid|last exit|program|working directory\"\nstate = running\nprogram = /Users/phaedrus/.openclaw/service-env/ai.openclaw.gateway-env-wrapper.sh\nworking directory = /Users/phaedrus/.openclaw\npid = 67683\nlast exit code = 0\n\n$ lsof -iTCP:18789 -sTCP:LISTEN -n -P\nnode 67683 phaedrus ... TCP 127.0.0.1:18789 (LISTEN)\nnode 67683 phaedrus ... TCP [::1]:18789 (LISTEN)\n\n$ tail -n 80 /Users/phaedrus/Library/Logs/openclaw/gateway.log\n2026-05-22T08:17:09.880-04:00 [gateway] http server listening (10 plugins: acpx, browser, canvas, codex, discord, exa, lossless-claw, memory-core, openai, telegram; 5.6s)\n2026-05-22T08:17:15.948-04:00 [gateway] ready\n```\n\n### Doctor Repair\n- Scenario: the active context engine is incompatible with every configured agent-run host.\n- Command/path exercised: doctor preview and repair tests.\n- Observed result: normal `doctor` reports missing host capabilities; `doctor --fix` rewrites `plugins.slots.contextEngine` to `\"legacy\"`. Mixed compatible/incompatible runtime configs warn without rewriting the global slot.\n",
        "branch": "josh/context-engine-host-compat",
